<section xml:id="soc" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0">
    <title>Summary of changes</title>
    <para>This section lists the changes of The &product; Administrator Guide.</para>
    <simplesect condition="pe" xml:id="pe-changes">
        <title>Version 7.0.6 - 7.0.7</title>
        <formalpara>
            <title>Changes in product:</title>
            <para/>
        </formalpara>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>The <parameter>logstore()</parameter> destination that was available only in &abbrev; version 6 is now available in version 7.0.7, allowing you to store messages in encrypted files. For more details, see <olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="destination-logstore"/>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>You can use password-protected private keys in the <parameter>network()</parameter> and <parameter>syslog()</parameter> source and destination drivers. For details, see <olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="tls-password-protected-keys"/>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <formalpara>
            <title>Changes in documentation:</title>
            <para/>
        </formalpara>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>A new section describing common error messages has been added to the document. For more information, see <olink targetptr="error-messages" targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin"/>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Several corrections and editorial changes.</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    </simplesect>
    <simplesect condition="pe">
        <title>Version 7.0.5 - 7.0.6</title>
        <formalpara>
            <title>Changes in product:</title>
            <para/>
        </formalpara>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>A new source called <parameter>windowsevent()</parameter> has been added. The <parameter>windowsevent()</parameter> source receives Windows event logs from the &wec; tool, which collects event logs from Windows hosts. For more information, see <olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="source-windowsevent"/>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Added a section about how to unset message fields and groups of fields. For more information, see <olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="rewrite-unset"/>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <formalpara>
            <title>Changes in documentation:</title>
            <para/>
        </formalpara>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>A new section describing common error messages has been added to the document. For more information, see <olink targetptr="error-messages" targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin"/>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Several corrections and editorial changes.</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    </simplesect>
    <simplesect condition="pe">
        <title>Version 7.0.4 - 7.0.5</title>
        <formalpara>
            <title>Changes in product:</title>
            <para/>
        </formalpara>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>&abbrev; now supports Oracle Linux 6 (x84_64). For details, see <olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="supported-platforms"/>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>A new <parameter>systemd-journal()</parameter> source option, called <parameter>read-old-records()</parameter>, has been added. For more information, see <olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="systemd-journal-options-read-old-records"/>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>An option called <parameter>jvm-options()</parameter> has been added, which allows you to fine-tune Java Virtual Machine settings when configuring Elasticsearch, HDFS, and Apache Kafka destinations. For details, see:</para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="reference-destination-elasticsearch"/></para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="reference-destination-elasticsearch2"/></para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="reference-destination-hdfs"/></para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="reference-destination-kafka"/></para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="reference-options"/></para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>A new HDFS destination option, called <parameter>hdfs-append-enabled()</parameter> has been added. For further information, see <olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="option-hdfs-append-enabled"/>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Macros are now supported in the <parameter>hdfs-file()</parameter> option. For details, see <olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="hdfs-option-hdfs-file"/>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>The following new TLS options have been added:</para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="tls-options-dhparam-file"/></para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="tls-options-ecdh-curve-list"/></para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>A new parser, capable of processing input in XML format, has been added. For more information, see <olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="xml-parser"/>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>A new parser, capable of parsing the log messages of various Cisco devices, has been added. For details, see <olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="cisco-parser"/>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <formalpara>
            <title>Changes in documentation:</title>
            <para/>
        </formalpara>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Added a section on upgrading from syslog-ng OSE to syslog-ng-PE. For more information, see <olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="upgrading-from-ose-to-pe"/>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Added warning about the requirement to delete the persist file once the <parameter>dir()</parameter> option of <parameter>disk-buffer()</parameter> has been modified or a new one has been added. For more information, see <olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="chapter-destinations"/>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Clarified information about the Python parser's <parameter>deinit()</parameter> method. It runs not only at a syslog-ng graceful stop, but at a reload too. For details, see <olink targetdoc="syslog-ng-pe-guide-admin" targetptr="python-parser-methods"/>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Reworked <xref linkend="section-multithreading-performance"/> to make information more accessible.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Several corrections and editorial changes.</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    </simplesect>
    <simplesect xml:id="pe-changes-703-704" condition="pe">
